                                New Arrivals




 
							Improve verbal and written communication skills using these language arts and discipline books. Available in a few media formats, these books feature advice and exercises designed to instill important language concepts such as grammar. They're appropriate for teaching others or personal development.All Reading LevelsNo matter which reading level a person possesses, there are language arts and discipline books designed to meet the individual's needs. Use word practice books to help those at elementary school reading levels comprehend and use words appropriately, or people at high school and above reading levels can turn to style guides to learn how to craft essays or business reports that clearly communicate their ideas.Variety of Media TypesThese language arts and discipline books come in several formats including audio, hardcover, paperback and compact disc. This makes it easier to integrate the lessons into your busy life. Listen to audio recordings of important language concepts during your daily commute, or use the books to study at home or keep in your bookcase for reference. The wide selection of options makes the books a great addition to classrooms and professional offices.Any Language Subject You NeedLanguage is a broad subject, and there are language arts and discipline books to cover almost every topic. Impress your friends or business associates with facts you learned from reading about the history of the English language, or study how to smoothly transition between ideas when writing reports, essays, or novels. Language books provide the first step to becoming an expert in a topic by bolstering your knowledge about a particular subject.


